DOC.brief_summary: The purpose of this study is to evaluate the safety and effectiveness of a new opthalmic viscoelastic material for the use in cataract surgery. The new viscoelastic will be compared to a currently marketed viscoelastic material.
DOC.brief_title: Clinical Evaluation of a New Viscoelastic for Cataract Surgery
DOC.criteria: Otherwise healthy eye with no pathology other than the presence of cataract Visual potential of 20/40 or better Taking any medications that affect vision, intraocular pressure or ease of cataract surgery (e.g. flomax, glaucoma medications, etc.) Known intraocular pressure increases from steroid treatment Low endothelial cell count
